<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="shape-vt">shape <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ʃeɪp/    美 /ʃeɪp/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>使成形：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>an L-shaped sofa 
L形的沙发</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Italy shaped like a boot lies in the south of Europe. 
意大利位于欧洲的南部，它的形状像一只靴子。</p><footer>人教⑧-1</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>影响 / 决定 (事物的发展)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s not what we do once in a while that shapes our lives, but what we do consistently. 
不是我们偶尔所做的而是我们一贯所做的事影响自己的一生。</p><footer>2011 湖南</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="shape-up">shape up</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[非正式用语] 改进 (行为 / 工作)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If he doesn’t shape up, he’ll soon be out of a job. 
如果他不改进的话，很快就会失业。</p></div></div>